 Provide broad legal support for the overall Digital & Technology businesses, including Technology Procurement, E-Commerce and Data & Analytics product teams. Independently negotiate contracts including SaaS, IP and technology license agreements, vendor agreements and SLAs. Develop expertise in relevant legal regimes, including data privacy laws, Intellectual Property, Artificial Intelligence and trade secret protection. Ensure ongoing alignment with client teams and across Yum! brands and assist in issue-spotting and problem-solving for potential legal issues outside of immediate expertise by building strong business relationships with key internal clients, primarily on the strategy, finance, operations, and technology teams. Assist in management of intellectual property portfolio. Work closely and productively with internal clients, outside counsel and external vendors. 
 
Education: Juris Doctor Degree from an ABA accredited law school 
 
Experience and Other Relevant Skills: 
 Licensed to practice law Strong background in contract drafting and negotiation, particularly technology contracts Experience working with clients at all levels of the organization Ability to work efficiently and independently, but also collaborative with colleagues across the organization, and handle conflicts, solve problems and/or propose solutions Detail and results oriented with excellent organizational and analytical skills Ability to communicate clearly and concisely Sound judgment, critical thinking and analytical skills Ability to prioritize and perform multiple tasks and handle changing priorities successfully in a fast-paced environment 
 
